instead—the book then examines the demand for biofuel and the effects of biofuel policies on agricultural price uncertainty. Also discussed are genetically engineered crops, which are assuming an increasingly important role in arbitrating tensions between energy production, environmental protection, and the global food supply. Other contributions discuss the major effects of genetic engineering on worldwide food markets. By addressing some of the most challenging topics at the intersection of agriculture and biotechnology, this volume informs crucial debates.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 30. Aug 2021) 0aAgricultural biotechnologyxGovernment policyxUnited States. 0aAgricultural biotechnologyxGovernment policyzUnited States. 0aAgricultural subsidiesxGovernment policyxUnited States. 0aAgricultural subsidiesxGovernment policyzUnited States. 0aAgriculture and energyxGovernment policyxUnited States. 0aAgriculture and energyxGovernment policyzUnited States. 0aAgriculture and statexUnited States. 0aAgriculture and statezUnited States. 0aBiomass energyxGovernment policyxUnited States. 0aBiomass energyxGovernment policyzUnited States. 0aCrop insurancexUnited States. 0aCrop insurancezUnited States. 7aBUSINESS & ECONOMICS / General.2bisacsh1 aBabcock, Bruce A., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBeckman, Jayson, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aChen, Xiaoguang, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGoodhue, Rachael E., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGoodwin, Barry K., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGraff Zivin, Joshua S., eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aHertel, Thomas W., econtributor.4ctb4https:/